        <description><![CDATA[<h3>Secrets Provisioning Request</h3>
<p>Request secure storage and management of application secrets, API keys, and credentials.</p>

<h4>What You'll Get:</h4>
<ul>
<li>HashiCorp Vault secret path created</li>
<li>Access policies configured</li>
<li>Kubernetes secret integration (External Secrets Operator)</li>
<li>Automatic secret rotation enabled</li>
<li>Audit logging configured</li>
<li>Access control policies (RBAC)</li>
<li>Secret versioning enabled</li>
</ul>

<h4>Prerequisites:</h4>
<ul>
<li>Service name and namespace</li>
<li>Secret type (database credentials, API keys, certificates, etc.)</li>
<li>Access requirements (which services need access)</li>
<li>Rotation policy preference</li>
</ul>

<h4>Approval Process:</h4>
<p>Security Engineer approval required for all secret provisioning requests.</p>

<h4>SLA:</h4>
<ul>
<li><strong>Fulfillment Time:</strong> 2 business hours</li>
<li><strong>Response Time:</strong> 30 minutes</li>
</ul>

<h4>Security Notes:</h4>
<ul>
<li>Secrets are encrypted at rest and in transit</li>
<li>Access is logged and audited</li>
<li>Automatic rotation policies enforced</li>
<li>Least-privilege access model</li>
</ul>

<h4>Tags:</h4>
<p>secrets-management, vault, security, kubernetes, encryption, compliance</p>]]></description>
